cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for sleep staging using raw EEG signals. This involves processing and analyzing large amounts of data, which is a common task in machine learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper focuses on the application of the proposed method to improve well-being, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Signal Processing (cs.SI).
